results.name: Number of divisors d of n for which 2*phi(d) > d.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
example: n = 105 has eight divisors: [1, 3, 5, 7, 15, 21, 35, 105]. When A083254 is applied to them, we obtain [1, 1, 3, 5, 1, 3, 13, -9], and seven of these numbers are positive, thus a(105) = 7.
xref: Differs from A001227 for the first time at n=105, where a(105) = 7, while A001227(105) = 8.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Sep 05 2018
